      <title>Atomic Arrangements in Solids</title>
      <description>This video/animation asks the question "So if  the same molecules are in the solid, liquid, and vapor forms of water, why are their properties so different?"  The properties of a material are affected not just by the kinds of atom in it, but also by how they are arranged, and how free they are to move around. Forms of carbon are introduced, from graphite to buckyballs. </description>
